CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 7, 1962, pg. 2 reads: "The Guardsmen - Courier photographer Charles (Teenie) Harris snapped this group of Legion of Guardsmen delegates meeting, this week in Pittsburgh. Officers shown are (front row, left to right) the Rev. William H. Bartlett, national chaplain, Massachusetts; Herman M. Silwenk, adjutant general, New York; William C. Cobbs, national commander, Pennsylvania; James Riley, national junior vice commander, Ohio, and Joseph J. Colaneri, national trustee, Rhode Island. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of sixteen Legion of Guardsmen, including officers, from left, front row: Rev. William H. Bartlett, Herman M. Silwenk, William C. Cobbs, James Riley, and Joseph J. Colaneri, posed in Webster Hall during national convention
